I am fine with a seller asking what ever they want for an item. It is up to them on what it will take to part with it. For the buyers part, "Dont Be Stupid"

Do your research and dont feed the dips that are ruining this site and the market.

postcontent: Weatherby Mark V (German Made), .300 Weatherby Mag. MORE PICTURES at our website. www.standardfirearms.com. This rifle is in overall excellent condition, ready for the serious collector or hunter who wants a great proven rifle to shoot. This rifle was manufactured in West Germany sometime between 1959-1973 since it has a "P" serial number. The serial number is P7286. The stock on this gun is nearly perfect with only one small area with chip in the finish. You can see the very minor chip in the pictures. This chip on the at the butt is really the only imperfections, as even handling marks are very, very faint. I would rate the stock at 95%+. The bluing looks like it did the day it left West Germany! The bluing looks perfect since I can’t see any imperfections at all. Even the butt pad is original and in like new condition. This rifle comes with one piece scope mounts and 1" rings. The scope mount looks like Leupold and late model since they are in a matt finish and don’t match the rifle. The length of pull measures about 13.5". The trigger pull (3 pull average) is 4.05lbs. The barrel measures 25.5". I scoped the barrel using a Hawkeye bore scope and the barrel looks like new with very sharp rifling, no rust, pitting or corrosion. There is some dust from being stored and a very minor build up of copper. The barrel looks like it has only been shot a few times! If you are looking for a German made Weatherby this is your chance at a very nice rifle.
